ls/item/memorial/17048|title=War Memorials Register, 2nd Battn Royal Sussex Regiment, 1882 to 1902 |date= |accessdate=4 April 2020|work=Imperial War Museum}}</ref><ref>{{NHLE |num=1043677 |desc= Bronze statue of Royal Sussex Regiment ... |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image = Statue of Godfrey, First Viscount Tredegar.jpg  \n| commonscat = Equestrian statue of Godfrey Morgan (Cardiff)\n| subject = [[Godfrey Morgan, 1st Viscount Tredegar]]   \n| location = Gorsedd Gardens, [[Cathays Park]], Cardiff \n| date = 1909\n| type = Equestrian statue on pedestal with reliefs\n| material = Bronze & stone\n| dimensions = \n| designation = Grade II\n| coordinates=\n| show_wikidata= yes\n| wikidata = Q29491649\n| notes = <ref>{{cadw|num=13665|desc= Statue of Godfrey, First Viscount Tredegar|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image = Memorial to the Engine Room Heroes Liverpool 1.jpg\n| commonscat = Memorial to the Heroes of the Engine Room\n| subject = [[Memorial to the Engine Room Heroes of the Titanic]]\n| location = Pier Head, [[Liverpool]]\n| date = 1916\n| type = Obelisk with statues \n| material = Bronze & stone\n| dimensions = \n| designation = Grade II*\n| coordinates=\n| show_wikidata= yes\n| wikidata = Q3305518\n| notes = <ref>{{cite web |author=|url= https://www.iwm.org.uk/memorials/item/memorial/1224|title=War Memorials Register, Engine Room Heroes (Titanic Memorial) |date= |accessdate=4 April 2020|work=Imperial War Museum}}</ref><ref>{{NHLE |num=1209973 |desc= Memorial to Heroes of the Marine Engine Room |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image = \n| commonscat = \n| subject = Lieutenant Colonel A. Carteret-Thynne DSO\n| location = Parish Church of St. James the Great, [[Kilkhampton]], Cornwall \n| date = 1917\n| type = Tablet with figure & plaque\n| material = Marble & bronze\n| dimensions = \n| designation = \n| coordinates=\n| show_wikidata= \n| wikidata = \n| notes = Carteret-Thynne was kille