ernarfon]]\n| date = 1921\n| type = Statue on plinth\n| material = Bronze & stone\n| dimensions = \n| designation = Grade II\n| coordinates=\n| show_wikidata= yes\n| wikidata = Q29483625\n| notes = AB Burton (foundary); Base by J Fletcher of Caernarfon.<ref>{{cadw |num= 3843 |desc=Statue of David Lloyd George |accessdate= 6 March 2020}}</ref>  \n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image = Northwich - John Brunner Statue.jpg \n| commonscat = \n| subject = [[Statue of Sir John Tomlinson Brunner]]\n| location = Grounds of Brunner-Mond works, [[Winnington]], [[Cheshire]]\n| date = 1922\n| type = Statue on pedestal\n| material = Bronze and granite\n| dimensions = \n| designation = Grade II\n| coordinates=\n| show_wikidata= yes\n| wikidata = Q15979536\n| notes = <ref>{{Cite book | author = Edward Morris & Emma Roberts| year = 2012 | title = Public Sculpture of Cheshire and Merseyside (excluding Liverpool)| volume = 15| series = Public Sculpture of Britain | publication-place = Liverpool| publisher = Liverpool University Press|isbn = 978-1-84631-492-6}}</ref><ref>{{NHLE |num= 1161131|desc= Statue of Sir John Brunner in front of Research Lab., Winnington Works|access-date= 6 March 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image = Thomas Charles Edwards statue, Aberystwyth 2014-09-09 - 2.jpg\n| commonscat = Statue of Thomas Charles Edwards, Aberystwyth\n| subject = [[Thomas Charles Edwards]]\n| location =[[Old College, Aberystwyth]]\n| date = 1922\n| type = Statue on pedestal\n| material = Bronze & granite\n| dimensions =\n| designation = Grade II\n| coordinates = \n| show_wikidata= yes\n| wikidata = Q29488944\n| notes = AB Burton (foundary)<ref>{{cadw |num= 10311 |desc= Statue of Thomas Edwards |accessdate= 5 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanderkrogt.net/statues/object.php?webpage=ST&record=gbwa086|title= Statue of Thomas Charles Edwards|website= Hither & Dither|date=27 July 2012 |access-date=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image = Llanelli War Memorial.jpg